      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": ["REFERENCE-GUIDED INPAINTING - FLUX.2 Klein 9B (companion to the Moebius examples)\n\nSame pipeline as the prompt example, plus a SECOND image input: the reference. Its latent is chained (ReferenceLatent) onto the conditioning, so Klein can bring the reference's subject/style INTO the masked area - 'insert this product into this scene', 'replace the sofa with the one from this photo'. Moebius cannot do this at all (no image-conditioning input, no text encoder) - it only removes.\n\nHow to use:\n1) Load the scene image, right-click -> Open in MaskEditor, paint WHERE the content should go.\n2) Load the reference image (the WHAT: object/subject/style to insert).\n3) Describe the insertion in the positive prompt (it steers how the reference is used), Queue.\n\nMODELS: same three as the prompt example - flux-2-klein-9b-fp8.safetensors (diffusion_models), qwen_3_8b_fp8mixed.safetensors (text_encoders), flux2-vae.safetensors (vae).\nEXTRA NODE PACK: ComfyUI-Inpaint-CropAndStitch by lquesada (https://github.com/lquesada/ComfyUI-Inpaint-CropAndStitch) - via ComfyUI-Manager or git clone into custom_nodes/.\n\nRule of thumb across the three examples in this folder:\n- remove something               -> Moebius (fastest, smallest)\n- replace with something DESCRIBED -> flux2 prompt inpaint\n- replace with something FROM A PHOTO -> this graph"],
      "color": "#233",
      "bgcolor": "#355",
      "title": "About this workflow"
    },
